race.comment: FAVOUR THE BOLD (7) returned for his second campaign with the two slick wins at Scone in fast time. Regular rider retains the mount and don't think he's hit his ceiling yet. Hard to stop with the weight drop. SOCIAL CIRCLE (5) another Scone-trained runner proven at this level. Failed narrowly when second to Petticoat two back at this level over the 1000m. Forced to work hard early when a tiring fourth over 1100m at Warwick Farm in a BM68. Kept fresh and since placed in a 900m Scone trial. Leading rider booked from the good gate. MADRINA (1) third-up for the new yard sat on the pace when pulled out to plenty to record a tenacious win over this trip at Kembla Grange. Senior rider booked and hard to stop again whilst in this form. DOLLY (6) resumed in weaker company when swooped late for a tough win over 1100m at Cootamundra. Clearly returned well and not to be overlooked. STAR PREDICTION (8) underrated gelding who can surprise a few of these with the light weight.
